013package org.apache.juneau.utils;
014
015import org.apache.juneau.common.utils.*;
016import org.apache.juneau.internal.*;
017
018/**
019 * Represents a simple tuple of 3 objects.
020 *
021 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
022 * </ul>
023 *
024 * @param <A> Object 1 type.
025 * @param <B> Object 2 type.
026 * @param <C> Object 3 type.
027 */
028public class Tuple3<A,B,C> {
029
030   /**
031    * Static creator.
032    *
033    * @param <A> Object 1 type.
034    * @param <B> Object 2 type.
035    * @param <C> Object 3 type.
036    * @param a Object 1.
037    * @param b Object 2.
038    * @param c Object 3.
039    * @return A new tuple object.
040    */
041   public static <A,B,C> Tuple3<A,B,C> of(A a, B b, C c) {
042      return new Tuple3<>(a,b,c);
043   }
044
045   private final A a;
046   private final B b;
047   private final C c;
048
049   /**
050    * Constructor.
051    *
052    * @param a Object 1.
053    * @param b Object 2.
054    * @param c Object 3.
055    */
056   public Tuple3(A a, B b, C c) {
057      this.a = a;
058      this.b = b;
059      this.c = c;
060   }
061
062   /**
063    * Returns the first object in this tuple.
064    *
065    * @return The first object in this tuple.
066    */
067   public A getA() {
068      return a;
069   }
070
071   /**
072    * Returns the second object in this tuple.
073    *
074    * @return The second object in this tuple.
075    */
076   public B getB() {
077      return b;
078   }
079
080   /**
081    * Returns the third object in this tuple.
082    *
083    * @return The third object in this tuple.
084    */
085   public C getC() {
086      return c;
087   }
088
089   @Override /* Object */
090   public int hashCode() {
091      return HashCode.of(a,b,c);
092   }
093
094   @Override /* Object */
095   public boolean equals(Object o) {
096      return o instanceof Tuple3 && Utils.eq(this, (Tuple3<?,?,?>)o, (x,y)->Utils.eq(x.a,y.a) && Utils.eq(x.b,y.b) && Utils.eq(x.c,y.c));
097   }
098}
